[19:03:56.510] Server  LOG     [{"id":"","role":"assistant","parts":[{"type":"step-start"},{"type":"text","text":"Ownership — that's the big one. I don't wait around for someone to hand me a task. I see something that needs fixing and I just go fix it.\n\nI bring a full-stack mindset too. I can jump into Figma and design something, build out the frontend in React/Next.js, wire up the backend, set up the database, and ship it to Vercel. That end-to-end ability means I'm not blocked waiting on someone else for every little thing.\n\nAt Bluon I've been doing this for almost 3 years — building RAG pipelines, architecting schemas for 200k+ chats, handling breaking production changes with zero data loss. At Moonwish I co-founded the studio, talked directly with clients, scoped projects, and shipped 8 websites. So I've seen both the startup scrappiness and the production engineering side.\n\nBut honestly, beyond the technical stuff — I genuinely care. I care about the people I work with, I ask a lot of questions early so we don't waste time going the wrong direction, and I'm not afraid to say \"I don't know\" when I don't know. I'd rather look dumb for five minutes than waste a week going the wrong way. That kind of honesty tends to make teams move faster :)\n\n<<<FOLLOWUPS>>>\n- What's the hardest problem you've solved at Bluon?\n- Can you tell me more about your experience with AI and RAG pipelines?\n- What does your full-stack workflow look like day to day?","state":"done"}]}]
